                    </disp-formula>
                </p>
                <p>Where:</p>
                <list list-type="bullet">
                    <list-item>
                        <p>N is the number of geographical units;</p>
                    </list-item>
                    <list-item>
                        <p>X
                            <sub>i</sub> is the variable describing the phenomenon under investigation in region i;</p>
                    </list-item>
                    <list-item>
                        <p>
                            <overline>
                                <italic toggle="yes">X</italic>
                            </overline> represents the sample average and (X
                            <sub>i</sub> &#x2013; 
                            <underline>X</underline>) it is the variable&#x2019;s average deviation;</p>
                    </list-item>
                    <list-item>
                        <p>
                            <inline-formula>
                                <mml:math display="inline" id="math9">
                                    <mml:mrow>
                                        <mml:msubsup>
                                            <mml:mtext>S</mml:mtext>
